
                                            The European playoffs in the next week are set to determine the last four spots ahead of the draw on 1 December.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - While the journey to the Fifa World Cup in Russia next year is heating up on the pitch, some teams are still sweating over qualification for footballs showpiece. The European playoffs in the next week are set to determine the last four spots ahead of the draw on 1 December. Those that do not have to sweat over qualification have unveiled their kits for the World Cup. The likes of Spain, Belgium, Argentina, hosts Russia and defending champions Germany will all don new attires.        